<p>[6] In that spirit, I&rsquo;d like to conclude this text with a poem by leading Israeli author Aharon Shabtai:<br /><br /><em>
I, too, have declared war:<br />
You&rsquo;ll need to divert part of the force<br />
deployed to wipe out the Arabs&mdash;<br />
to drive them out of their homes<br />
and expropriate their land&mdash;<br />
and set it against me.<br />
You&rsquo;ve got tanks and places,<br />
and soldiers by the battalion;<br />
you&rsquo;ve got the rams&rsquo; horns in your hands<br />
with which to rouse the masses;<br />
you&rsquo;ve got men to interrogate and torture;<br />
you&rsquo;ve got cells for detention.<br />
I have only this heart<br />
with which I give shelter<br />
